ce:section.ce:para:
To optimize the detection conditions, the effect of incubation time on the change (ΔIp) in the DPV peak current were studied in the PBS (pH 7.4). Fig. 8
                         presents the relationship curve of the ΔIp value with the incubation time. It can be seen From Fig. 8 that the ΔIp value increases with increase of the incubation time when the time is less than 30 min. With the increase of incubation time, more cancer cells will be captured by FA/Glu-GQD-Pd@Au and leads to an increased ΔIp value. However, the value tends to the maximum and then remains almost unchanged when the time is more than 30 min. This proves that the capture process for cancer cells is close to complete. To obtain a high sensitivity and save the detection time, 30 min of the incubation time was used for electrochemical detection of cancer cells (Fig. 9
                        ).
